The paper deals with the intersection of biometrics and cryptography, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The specific biometric being studied is iris recognition, which involves image processing and computer vision techniques (cs.CV). The paper also discusses error-correcting codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The experiments conducted on the iris challenge evaluation (ICE) database involve machine learning and pattern recognition techniques (cs.MM), and the paper discusses the performance of the decoding algorithm, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
